Sentencas: Y2O3-Sm2O3 co-doped ceria (YSDC) powder was synthesized by a gel-casting method using Ce(NO3)(3)center dot 6H(2)O, Sm2O3 and Y2O3 as raw materials.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Y2O3-Sm2O3 co-doped ceria electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Phase structure of the synthesized powders was characterized by X-Ray diffraction analysis.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Y2O3-Sm2O3 co-doped ceria electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Sinterability of the powders was investigated by testing the relative density and observing the microstructure of the sintered YSDC samples.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Y2O3-Sm2O3 co-doped ceria electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Electrical conductivity of the sintered YSDC samples was measured using impedance spectra method.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Y2O3-Sm2O3 co-doped ceria electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Single solid oxide fuel cells based on the YSDC electrolyte were also assembled and tested.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Y2O3-Sm2O3 co-doped ceria electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The results showed that YSDC powders with single-phase fluorite structure can be obtained by calcining the dried gelcasts at temperature above 800 degrees C. Average particle size of the YSDC powder is 50-100 nm.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Y2O3-Sm2O3 co-doped ceria electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Relative density of more than 95% of the theoretical can be achieved by sintering the YSDC compacts at temperature above 1400 degrees C.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Y2O3-Sm2O3 co-doped ceria electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The sintered YSDC sample has an ionic conductivity of 4.74 x 10(-2)
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Y2O3-Sm2O3 co-doped ceria electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: S cm(-1) at 800 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Y2O3-Sm2O3 co-doped ceria electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Single fuel cells based on the YSDC electrolyte with 50 mu m in thickness were tested using humidified hydrogen as fuel and air as oxidant, and maximum power densities of about 190 and 112 mW cm(-2) were achieved at 700 and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Y2O3-Sm2O3 co-doped ceria electrolyte for IT-SOFCs
